<p>I'm trying to take a single file object and split it into chunks by a specified chunk size. In my example, trying to split a single file into 1MB chunks. So I figure out how many chunks it would take, then I'm trying to slice the file starting from the 'offset' (current chunk I'm on * chunk size), and slicing off a chunk size. My first slice comes out properly at 1MB but my subsequent slices turn out to 0, any ideas why? Have a working codepen here: </p>  <p><a href="http://codepen.io/ngalluzzo/pen/VvpYKz?editors=001[1]" rel="nofollow">http://codepen.io/ngalluzzo/pen/VvpYKz?editors=001[1]</a></p>  <pre><code>var file = $('#uploadFile')[0].files[0];   var chunkSize = 1024 * 1024;   var fileSize = file.size;   var chunks = Math.ceil(file.size/chunkSize,chunkSize);   var chunk = 0;    console.log('file size..',fileSize);   console.log('chunks...',chunks);    while (chunk &lt;= chunks) {       var offset = chunk*chunkSize;       console.log('current chunk..', chunk);       console.log('offset...', chunk*chunkSize);       console.log('file blob from offset...', offset)       console.log(file.slice(offset,chunkSize));       chunk++;   } </code></pre>